    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1995) - ENGINE CONTROL SYSTEM OVERVIEW - INJECTOR DRIVER MODULE
        - III. OUTPUT DRIVER FOR THE INJECTORS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>III. OUTPUT DRIVER FOR THE INJECTORS</title>
        <para>The IDM controls when the injector is turned on and how long the injector is turned on by closing the
            circuit to ground by the use of output driver transistors.
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1450116">1.16</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            Each injector has an individual output driver in the IDM. The processor in the IDM selects the correct
            firing sequence, the ECM through the FDCS signal controls the timing of when the injection starts and the
            duration of how long the injector is open.
        </para>
        <figure id="ef1450116" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg1105" filename="../figeg1/EG1105.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 1.16 - Injector Driver Module (Output Driver)</caption>
        </figure>
